claims.text:
A method for optimizing heat dissipation in electronic devices using a cooling system (200), comprising:
receiving real-time performance feedback from the electronic device;
adapting the architecture of the cooling system based on the real-time performance feedback using a dynamic learning model (201);
processing structured and unstructured data seamlessly through a hybrid data processing approach (202);
ensuring adherence to predefined ethical guidelines and norms in AI decisions through an ethical decision-making module (203);
autonomously identifying and correcting errors in algorithms using a self-repair mechanism (204);
enhancing processing speed and efficiency in data handling using quantum computing principles (205); and
operating the AI across different operating systems and hardware seamlessly through a cross-platform integration framework (206).
The method is characterized by adapting the architecture of the cooling system based on real-time performance feedback using a dynamic learning model (201).

